From df2cc66902d2b2f26b8ffcafb36af182d3156d87 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.local>
Date: Sat, 11 Apr 2026 22:39:37 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Branch-scoped schedule view and auto-schedule
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Supervisors can now work on a single branch at a time:

1. Daily view branch filter
   The existing All / Shuhada / Salam / Salwa buttons above the pool now
   also filter the schedule grid. Slots belonging entirely to another
   branch render as muted 'Other branch' placeholders so the supervisor
   sees the slot is taken but does not see or touch its contents. Mixed
   double/triple/group slots that contain at least one student from the
   selected branch render in full. A blue banner at the top of the grid
   shows which branch is currently being viewed.

2. Branch-scoped auto-schedule
   The auto-schedule modal now has a 'Scope' dropdown. Picking a branch
   limits the run to that branch's pool students — other branches stay
   untouched. When combined with 'Clear the existing schedule first',
   the reset is also scoped: only the selected branch's existing drops,
   pickups, and group/double slots get cleared via clearBranchFromSched,
   so supervisors can re-run auto-schedule per branch safely and then
   hand-tweak the result.

The scope dropdown defaults to whatever branch filter the supervisor
already has open on the pool, so it's one click to 'auto-schedule what
I'm looking at'. Three regression tests added (tests 25–27).
